MBOMBELA – The Department of Home Affairs says it has been experiencing abnormally high volumes of clients in the Mbombela office lately. For at least a week, people could be seen queuing around the block early in the morning in lines much longer than usual. Dorris Chiloane, acting provincial manager for the Department of Home Affairs, said they were closely monitoring the situation. “We are doing our best in ensuring that we assist the clients. Our staff members are even knocking off late so that we can have the clients assisted,” she said. READ MORE: Home affairs back to handling affairs AND Home Affairs officials start picketing before strike 